org.eclipse.viatra.query.runtime.base.itc.igraph

Interface IGraphDataSource<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of the nodes in the graph
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IBiDirectionalGraphDataSource<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Graph, IBiDirectionalWrapper

    public interface IGraphDataSource<V>
extends java.io.Serializable
    The interface prescribes the set of operations that a graph data source must support.

    Note that the old version of the interface is broken at version 1.6; MultiSets are now presented as Maps instead of Lists.

      • getTargetNodes

        java.util.Map<V,java.lang.Integer> getTargetNodes(V source)
        Returns the target nodes for the given source node. The returned data structure is a map (essentially a MultiSet) because of potential parallel edges in the graph data source. The values in the returned map represent the count of the given (source, target) edge. The method must not return null.
        Parameters:
        source - the source node
        Returns:
        the target nodes with their count values
        Since:
        1.6
